your voice.

106
00:11:31,259 --> 00:11:35,297
Going with dad was a bad idea,
and I miss our house.

107
00:11:36,565 --> 00:11:39,868
I'm short on money, but I'm
gonna try to come home soon.

108
00:11:51,346 --> 00:11:53,116
<i>I know it's been tough.</i>

109
00:11:53,215 --> 00:11:55,484
<i>But we are very happy</i>
<i>you're here.</i>

110
00:11:57,552 --> 00:11:58,854
Excuse me.

111
00:11:59,921 --> 00:12:01,790
Gretchen, my dear.

112
00:12:02,691 --> 00:12:04,093
I, uh...

113
00:12:04,526 --> 00:12:08,664
<i>I've been thinking,</i>
<i>for a young woman like you</i>

114
00:12:08,764 --> 00:12:13,735
there's... not so many things
to do here during the summer,
and so...

115
00:12:14,903 --> 00:12:17,205
I have a little idea.

116
00:12:17,739 --> 00:12:22,277
<i>A proposal. How would you like</i>
<i>to come work for me</i>
<i>at the resort?</i>

117
00:12:22,544 --> 00:12:23,980
<i>Oh, Herr König...</i>

118
00:12:24,246 --> 00:12:25,547
<i>Well,</i>
<i>it's an easy job,</i>

119
00:12:25,647 --> 00:12:27,449
<i>and it will give you</i>
<i>something to do</i>

120
00:12:27,549 --> 00:12:29,384
<i>while your parents build</i>
<i>the new resort for me.</i>

121
00:12:29,551 --> 00:12:32,254
I could use some more
English-speaking staff.

122
00:12:32,354 --> 00:12:34,189
Herr König, I think Gretchen...

123
00:12:34,356 --> 00:12:36,159
I would pay you
an appropriate salary,
of course.

124
00:12:36,258 --> 00:12:38,560
<i>I don't...</i>
- Yeah, sure. I'll do it.

125
00:12:44,900 --> 00:12:46,201
Oh.

126
00:12:46,802 --> 00:12:47,703
Schön.

127
00:12:48,203 --> 00:12:49,337
<i>Wonderful.</i>

128
00:12:49,504 --> 00:12:52,307
<i>Come by the reception tomorrow.</i>

129
00:12:54,576 --> 00:12:56,411
<i>Here's your ID badge,</i>
<i>sir.</i>

130
00:12:56,511 --> 00:12:59,281
<i>Would you like to pay</i>
<i>with cash or credit card?</i>

131
00:13:02,818 --> 00:13:04,486
Cash, or credit?

132
00:13:06,288 --> 00:13:07,489
Cash.

133
00:13:07,923 --> 00:13:10,859
"That will be
45 euro for a single room."

134
00:13:11,326 --> 00:13:14,896
Uh, that will be 45 euro
for a single room.

135
00:13:17,499 --> 00:13:20,036
Oh, and this is Beatrice

136
00:13:20,136 --> 00:13:22,437
and I am Gretchen.

137
00:13:22,469 --> 00:13:23,553
<font color="#ffff54">Can I go now?</font>

138
00:13:23,678 --> 00:13:24,554
<font color="#ffff54">No.</font>

139
00:13:24,679 --> 00:13:29,142
<font color="#ffff54">You can help me teach Gretchen
how to sell things in the shop.</font>

140
00:13:30,912 --> 00:13:34,750
<i>You have to be polite</i>
<i>and friendly,</i>
<i>even if the guest is rude.</i>

141
00:13:35,151 --> 00:13:37,753
<i>And remember to put up the sign</i>
<i>if you go to the bathroom.</i>

142
00:13:37,919 --> 00:13:41,323
But if you have
any real trouble,
just call the boss.

143
00:13:41,656 --> 00:13:44,860
He lives up the resort street,
on the hill.

144
00:13:46,394 --> 00:13:48,563
He lives in a vacation
bungalow?

145
00:13:49,297 --> 00:13:52,001
No, he has a villa way up there.

146
00:13:52,334 --> 00:13:54,536
He bought the hotel,
and so the bungalows

147
00:13:54,636 --> 00:13:57,405
are basically in the front yard
of his villa.

148
00:13:58,273 --> 00:13:59,908
Weird, right?

149
00:14:00,076 --> 00:14:01,110
Super.

150
00:14:08,682 --> 00:14:10,016
<font color="#ffff54">I'm so sorry.</font>

151
00:14:10,141 --> 00:14:11,851
<font color="#ffff54">No problem.</font>

152
00:14:12,521 --> 00:14:14,556
This happens
sometimes.

153
00:14:17,893 --> 00:14:20,328
How's your first day, my dear?

154
00:14:23,899 --> 00:14:25,400
Can't complain.

155
00:14:25,801 --> 00:14:28,037
And how is your German
coming along?

156
00:14:29,304 --> 00:14:30,772
Not good.

157
00:14:31,907 --> 00:14:33,176
This is okay.

158
00:14:33,408 --> 00:14:36,078
You know, there are
English-speaking schools

159
00:14:36,179 --> 00:14:38,281
over the border, in Italy.

160
00:14:43,451 --> 00:14:47,622
Well, I'll be along
to pick you up in one hour.

161
00:14:50,026 --> 00:14:51,760
Oh, I have my bike.

162
00:14:51,860 --> 00:14:52,861
Oh?

163
00:14:53,628 --> 00:14:54,629
No.

164
00:14:55,298 --> 00:14:56,398
No, no, no.

165
00:14:57,699 --> 00:15:00,836
<i>No, it will be too dark</i>
<i>on the country roads by then.</i>

166
00:15:00,936 --> 00:15:03,405
<i>This is why you</i>
<i>will not work late.</i>

167
00:15:03,973 --> 00:15:06,842
You will help Beatrix
with the peak times.

168
00:15:06,942 --> 00:15:08,376
What?

169
00:15:08,543 --> 00:15:11,346
I thought we were going to split
the evening shifts.

170
00:15:12,982 --> 00:15:14,317
<i>-You have a car.</i>

171
00:15:14,482 --> 00:15:15,952
<i>-I have a life, too.</i>

172
00:15:17,786 --> 00:15:20,189
Beatrix, I will not get drawn
into another debate with you.

173
00:15:20,289 --> 00:15:21,690
I don't wanna have
a debate with you.

174
00:15:21,790 --> 00:15:24,359
<i>-No. Every time I raise</i>
<i>an issue with you,</i>

175
00:15:24,459 --> 00:15:26,295
<i>there is something</i>
<i>you have to say about it.</i>

176
00:15:26,394 --> 00:15:28,463
<i>-I do everything you ask!</i>
<i>-No.</i>

177
00:15:28,563 --> 00:15:30,066
<i>-What? I work every day</i>
<i>late shifts!</i>

178
00:15:30,233 --> 00:15:31,867
<i>-You're blasting your</i>
<i>Scheisse music on the car radio</i>

179
00:15:31,968 --> 00:15:33,135
<i>on your way to work.</i>

180
00:15:33,236 --> 00:15:35,171
<i>I hear it across the forest.</i>

181
00:15:35,271 --> 00:15:36,738
<i>This is a nature reserve</i>

182
00:15:36,838 --> 00:15:38,207
<i>and you are disturbing</i>
<i>the wildlife</i>

183
00:15:38,307 --> 00:15:39,941
<i>with your 'boom, boom...'</i>

184
00:16:08,703 --> 00:16:12,174
They can dance on the carpet...

185
