<i>Gretchen?</i>

475
00:51:36,999 --> 00:51:38,533
Did we wake you?

476
00:51:45,707 --> 00:51:50,012
<i>All the owls</i>
<i>have individual calls</i>

477
00:51:50,246 --> 00:51:53,782
<i>so that they can understand</i>
<i>each other over long distances.</i>

478
00:51:54,150 --> 00:51:55,950
<i>And maybe we</i>
<i>can make a secret call</i>

479
00:51:56,052 --> 00:51:59,021
so that we
can understand each other.

480
00:51:59,821 --> 00:52:02,124
Now, I brought you something.

481
00:52:02,324 --> 00:52:04,293
I know that you will like this.

482
00:52:13,335 --> 00:52:15,237
Gretchen, come sit with us.

483
00:52:15,337 --> 00:52:16,472
Gretchen?

484
00:52:16,638 --> 00:52:18,807
I'm so sorry, did we wake you?

485
00:52:21,843 --> 00:52:22,710
No.

486
00:52:22,911 --> 00:52:25,780
Okay, good. Please join us.

487
00:52:27,316 --> 00:52:28,850
I went out last night.

488
00:52:30,319 --> 00:52:32,054
Where did you go?

489
00:52:32,354 --> 00:52:33,956
<i>The resort.</i>

490
00:52:35,790 --> 00:52:38,194
What were you doing there?

491
00:52:38,294 --> 00:52:40,029
I was with Trixie.

492
00:52:40,628 --> 00:52:41,896
<i>-Hm.</i>

493
00:52:42,364 --> 00:52:46,068
I didn't know Beatrix
was working late last night.

494
00:52:46,335 --> 00:52:48,370
<i>-She wasn't.</i>

495
00:52:48,471 --> 00:52:51,440
She was really confused.

496
00:52:51,540 --> 00:52:53,042
Come to think of it,
a lot like the guest

497
00:52:53,142 --> 00:52:55,411
we spoke about over the phone
the other night.

498
00:52:55,677 --> 00:52:58,447
Hm. I will look into this.

499
00:52:58,746 --> 00:53:01,783
Why is there nobody
working the reception after ten?

500
00:53:02,284 --> 00:53:05,521
<i>Seems like a lot of people</i>
<i>need assistance after ten.</i>

501
00:53:05,787 --> 00:53:07,822
It doesn't make sense
economically.

502
00:53:07,990 --> 00:53:10,459
- That's stupid, it's a hotel.
<i>- Gretchen!</i>

503
00:53:10,559 --> 00:53:11,693
I can show you the numbers
if you like.

504
00:53:11,793 --> 00:53:13,395
It's not so interesting, but...

505
00:53:13,496 --> 00:53:15,064
Maybe another time.

506
00:53:17,099 --> 00:53:18,733
It's quite the place
you got here.

507
00:53:18,833 --> 00:53:20,369
-Gretchen, what's the matter?

508
00:53:20,536 --> 00:53:22,104
Why did you bring us here?

509
00:53:28,910 --> 00:53:31,547
Your parents are planning a--

510
00:53:31,646 --> 00:53:33,115
A new resort, I know.

511
00:53:35,717 --> 00:53:37,153
Why do we have to live here?

512
00:53:37,253 --> 00:53:38,053
<i>Gretchen!</i>

513
00:53:38,786 --> 00:53:39,821
Because it's pretty outside?

514
00:53:39,921 --> 00:53:42,158
Calm down, right now.

515
00:54:00,675 --> 00:54:03,445
You are here because your family
belongs here.

516
00:54:08,050 --> 00:54:10,052
That's a fucking weird way
to put it!

517
00:54:10,286 --> 00:54:13,122
Gretchen, that's enough!
What has gotten into you?
<i>-I don't know dad!</i>

518
00:54:13,222 --> 00:54:15,790
I'm just reflecting
on this very fucking weird
living situation

519
00:54:15,890 --> 00:54:17,892
that everybody just seems
to be cool with.

520
00:54:17,993 --> 00:54:18,994
Out!

521
00:54:19,361 --> 00:54:20,262
<i>Now!</i>

522
00:54:21,896 --> 00:54:23,966
- Great.
<i>- No, no, Luis.</i>

523
00:54:24,066 --> 00:54:26,101
A gentleman knows
when it's time to leave.

524
00:54:26,202 --> 00:54:27,970
You need some family time,
I understand.

525
00:54:28,070 --> 00:54:29,938
No, no, no, Herr König,
we don't want you to leave.

526
00:54:30,039 --> 00:54:31,906
It's alright, thank you
for the wonderful afternoon

527
00:54:32,007 --> 00:54:34,310
and I wish you a good evening.
-I'm very sorry.

528
00:54:34,410 --> 00:54:36,711
No, Luis, we are
so very happy to have you here.

529
00:54:36,811 --> 00:54:39,215
We've been desperately eager
for you to be here.

530
00:54:39,381 --> 00:54:43,619
And Gretchen, if there
is anything that... bothers you,

531
00:54:43,718 --> 00:54:45,787
don't be afraid to...

532
00:54:46,555 --> 00:54:48,123
talk to me.

533
00:54:50,259 --> 00:54:53,162
Oh, I leave your package
just here.

534
00:54:54,762 --> 00:54:57,066
Oh... it was a surprise.

535
00:54:57,166 --> 00:54:59,368
I was not supposed
to say anything.

536
00:54:59,468 --> 00:55:00,502
I am so sorry.

537
00:55:00,603 --> 00:55:02,037
What package?

538
00:55:03,405 --> 00:55:06,408
What package?
-It has your family name on it.

539
00:55:20,089 --> 00:55:22,191
It was your mother's stuff.

540
00:55:23,726 --> 00:55:25,793
<i>The small stuff, at least.</i>

541
00:55:26,095 --> 00:55:27,929
I received it this morning.

542
00:55:28,030 --> 00:55:30,798
<i>I... your father should perhaps</i>
<i>change the address</i>

543
00:55:30,898 --> 00:55:32,268
<i>on the counter...</i>

544
00:55:32,501 --> 00:55:34,370
What is it doing here, dad?

545
00:55:39,774 --> 00:55:41,277
I sold the old house.

546
00:55:46,682 --> 00:55:49,752
It was... still my house.

547
00:55:49,851 --> 00:55:52,254
<i>And I put the money</i>
<i>in an account for you.</i>

548
00:55:55,291 --> 00:55:58,627
<i>I... I didn't want you</i>
<i>to get worked up again--</i>

549
00:56:07,802 --> 00:56:10,472
<i>Hi,</i>
<i>you have reached</i>
<i>the Vanderkurt residence.</i>

550
00:56:10,572 --> 00:56:13,242
<i>Neither Gretchen nor Olivia</i>
<i>are here now,</i>

551
00:56:13,342 --> 00:56:15,810
<i>but we are dying to hear</i>
<i>what you have to say,</i>

552
00:56:15,910 --> 00:56:18,013
<i>so get ready to say it.</i>

553
00:56:18,314 --> 00:56:21,417
<i>Mom, I really wanna come home.</i>

554
00:56:22,785 --> 00:56:24,720
<i>It's really bad.</i>

555
00:56:28,691 --> 00:56:30,858
<i>I really want to come home.</i>

556
00:56:36,065 --> 00:56:37,533
<i>What do you think?</i>

557
00:56:42,738 --> 00:56:44,807
<i>What do you think, mom?</i>

558
00:56:45,441 --> 00:56:47,875
<i>What's your take</i>
<i>on that, mom?</i>

559
00:57:05,027 --> 00:57:07,429
<i>Next message.</i>

560
00:57:09,365 --> 00:57:12,934
<i>Hello Ms. Vanderkurt,</i>
<i>my name is Alma.</i>

561
00:57:13,235 --> 00:57:15,903
<i>I'm calling you</i>
<i>because of my sister, Gretchen.</i>

562
00:57:16,338 --> 00:57:18,540
<i>Gretchen calls you</i>
<i>when she feels bad,</i>

563
00:57:18,640 --> 00:57:20,442
<i>but you never answer.</i>

564
00:57:20,642 --> 00:57:22,444
<i>I can hear her from my room.</i>

565
00:57:22,978 --> 00:57:24,413
<i>I'm worried.</i>

566
00:57:24,580 --> 00:57:25,947
<i>If you get my message,</i>

567
00:57:26,148 --> 00:57:28,550
<i>I want you to call Gretchen</i>
<i>back on the phone.</i>

568
00:57:29,118 --> 00:57:31,353
<i>You can tell her</i>
<i>that you love her.</i>

569
00:57:31,754 --> 00:57:33,355
<i>It would mean a lot to her.</i>

570
00:57:34,022 --> 00:57:35,758
<i>It would make her happy.</i>

571
00:57:36,125 --> 00:57:38,827
<i>If you'd like to,</i>
<i>you can come visit us.</i>

572
00:57:39,294 --> 00:57:41,296
<i>You are always welcome here.</i>

573
00:58:01,250 --> 00:58:03,352
Good, you're packed.

574
00:58:04,952 --> 00:58:06,955
Do you even know how to drive?

575
00:58:08,056 --> 00:58:09,924
Where is everybody?

576
00:58:12,261 --> 00:58:15,097
They're at the hospital
with Dr. Bonomo.

577
00:58:15,264 --> 00:58:18,367
Alma had a very strong seizure.

578
00:58:20,035 --> 00:58:22,504
<i>It's your fault, Gretchen.</i>
<i>You know that.</i>

579
00:58:22,671 --> 00:58:24,473
<i>You terrified her.</i>

580
00:58:26,041 --> 00:58:30,646
I want you now
to write a farewell note.

581
00:58:31,313 --> 00:58:33,882
Then we will pick up
some money for you at my house

582
00:58:33,982 --> 00:58:35,784
and I'll drive you
to the station.

583
00:58:35,884 --> 00:58:37,952
The last train leaves
in one hour.

584
00:58:54,837 --> 00:58:56,738
Bring your bike.

585
00:59:27,002 --> 00:59:28,203
You like it?

586
00:59:29,338 --> 00:59:30,472
Sure.

587
00:59:30,772 --> 00:59:33,642
<i>You know it? A common cuckoo.</i>

588
00:59:34,776 --> 00:59:36,645
<i>A magnificent creature.</i>

589
00:59:38,080 --> 00:59:39,214
<i>-Common.</i>

590
00:59:39,915 --> 00:59:44,686
Ah. But its behavior is not.

591
00:59:44,786 --> 00:59:47,823
Its nature is quite remarkable.

592
00:59:49,625 --> 00:59:53,095
A nature modern man
destroys by disregard.

593
00:59:53,428 --> 00:59:58,267
<i>Some species need our help</i>
<i>to survive and reproduce.</i>

594
01:00:00,335 --> 01:00:02,804
I'm a preservationist, you know?

595
01:00:23,058 --> 01:00:24,593
<i>Oh, come along now.</i>

596
01:00:24,693 --> 01:00:29,364
<i>I want you to understand</i>
<i>who you got involved with.</i>

597
01:00:29,798 --> 01:00:33,869
Herr Lando here
was trespassing on my property

598
01:00:33,970 --> 01:00:36,104
<i>with an illegal firearm.</i>

599
01:00:36,204 --> 01:00:37,974
What are you doing?

600
01:00:38,073 --> 01:00:39,374
He's a cop.

601
01:00:40,943 --> 01:00:42,844
No, he's not.

602
01:00:43,512 --> 01:00:45,014
Not anymore.

603
01:00:45,247 --> 01:00:47,449
<i>You see, Erik here...</i>

604
01:00:47,716 --> 01:00:49,618
is actually a policeman.

605
01:00:49,851 --> 01:00:53,188
He has access to police files.

606
01:00:53,589 --> 01:00:57,092
Herr Lando was recently
discharged

607
01:00:57,192 --> 01:01:00,429
when they found out
he was investigating a case,

608
01:01:00,562 --> 01:01:04,600
<i>one that he is personally</i>
<i>involved with.</i>

609
01:01:04,766 --> 01:01:09,104
Okay, Erik. I think it is time
to take Herr Lando
to the police station.

610
01:01:09,271 --> 01:01:11,406
Gretchen, let's get your money.

611
01:01:15,944 --> 01:01:17,646
<i>This way, please.</i>

612
01:01:18,580 --> 01:01:20,248
Come along, now.

613
01:02:19,875 --> 01:02:23,779
<i>You are a liability, Gretchen.</i>
<i>I can't let you out.</i>

614
01:02:24,680 --> 01:02:27,249
What the fuck did you spray
me with?

615
01:02:27,349 --> 01:02:29,184
<i>-Just pheromones.</i>

616
01:02:29,284 --> 01:02:31,887
<i>I am giving you the chance</i>
<i>to be of great use</i>

617
01:02:31,988 --> 01:02:34,189
<i>in our quest for preservation.</i>

618
01:02:34,656 --> 01:02:37,225
<i>The adolescent</i>
<i>needs to be trained.</i>

619
01:02:40,195 --> 01:02:41,964
<i>Consider yourself lucky.</i>

620
01:02:51,473 --> 01:02:53,809
It's a mild sedative.

621
01:02:53,909 --> 01:02:55,210
What?

622
01:02:55,377 --> 01:02:57,846
It'll make Alma sleep
through the night.

623
01:03:03,251 --> 01:03:05,287
I'm staying here tonight.

624
01:03:08,356 --> 01:03:12,227
<i>These creatures can't speak</i>
<i>like you or I.</i>

625
01:03:12,394 --> 01:03:13,829
<i>But when trained,</i>

626
01:03:13,929 --> 01:03:18,201
<i>their song can be dizzyingly</i>
<i>persuasive.</i>

627
01:04:39,293 --> 01:04:41,878
<font color="#ffff54">No, no! Stay focused!</font>

628
01:05:17,914 --> 01:05:19,666
<font color="#ffff54">That's enough for today.</font>

629
01:05:40,312 --> 01:05:41,647
<font color="#ffff54">Come here.</font>

630
01:05:46,848 --> 01:05:47,716
<i>Ah, ah, ah.</i>

631
01:05:51,720 --> 01:05:53,822
Something
is not right.

632
01:06:06,004 --> 01:06:11,134
<font color="#ffff54">It is always something of a confirmation
of my dreams and good intentions.</font>

633
01:06:14,709 --> 01:06:16,245
Gretchen, your parents
need to hurry up

634
01:06:16,345 --> 01:06:17,779
with those construction plans.

635
01:06:17,879 --> 01:06:20,649
This one needs her own
mating grounds soon, no?

636
01:06:22,450 --> 01:06:25,187
And you know what else
she needs, Erik?

637
01:06:26,022 --> 01:06:27,957
<i>What happened</i>
<i>to Herr Lando's wife</i>

638
01:06:28,057 --> 01:06:30,126
<i>must not repeat itself.</i>

639
01:06:33,262 --> 01:06:37,033
<i>I'm very sorry</i>
<i>for what happened</i>
<i>to your wife, Herr Lando.</i>

640
01:06:37,366 --> 01:06:43,638
But this one's mother
wandered off my area
of authority.

641
01:06:43,738 --> 01:06:48,077
She got nervous
when this one left the nest

642
01:06:48,244 --> 01:06:50,478
<i>before we had another offspring</i>

643
01:06:50,578 --> 01:06:51,981
ready to replace her.

644
01:06:52,348 --> 01:06:55,850
<i>There were family matters</i>
<i>prolonging my endeavor.</i>

645
01:07:00,922 --> 01:07:02,457
Actually...

646
01:07:02,824 --> 01:07:06,461
Are you aware that
you have had the good fortune

647
01:07:06,561 --> 01:07:10,765
to witness three laying
ceremonies as of now?

648
01:07:10,865 --> 01:07:11,833
Wow.

649
01:07:12,268 --> 01:07:15,972
Most people don't get
to attend a single one.

650
01:07:16,538 --> 01:07:19,141
And those that do
don't remember that they did.

651
01:07:19,507 --> 01:07:25,247
<i>A sacred process that keeps</i>
<i>an ancient creature alive</i>
<i>and well.</i>

652
01:07:25,714 --> 01:07:28,717
<i>A magnificent creature</i>
<i>whose approach to family</i>

653
01:07:28,817 --> 01:07:31,988
<i>is beyond human comprehension.</i>

654
01:07:34,622 --> 01:07:36,591
Which brings me back to you,
Erik.

655
01:07:36,691 --> 01:07:39,561
You will get Beatrix
ready to conceive.

656
01:07:40,062 --> 01:07:43,099
<i>Consider your mishap last night</i>
<i>a dry run.</i>

657
01:07:48,803 --> 01:07:49,938
Erik?

658
01:07:51,443 --> 01:07:53,570
<font color="#ffff54">I told him, not in the house.</font>

659
01:08:04,420 --> 01:08:06,055
Shh...

660
01:08:13,362 --> 01:08:14,562
Oh.

661
01:08:15,258 --> 01:08:16,218
<font color="#ffff54">Stay here.</font>

662
01:08:16,664 --> 01:08:18,367
No, no, no, no.

663
01:08:18,666 --> 01:08:20,336
<i>You should be on your side.</i>

664
01:08:20,436 --> 01:08:22,171
<i>You could choke, my dear.</i>

665
01:08:36,238 --> 01:08:37,614
<font color="#ffff54">No!</font>

666
01:08:54,003 --> 01:08:56,205
<i>Honey?</i>
<i>Honey, what's wrong?</i>

667
01:08:56,305 --> 01:08:58,140
I don't feel so good.

668
01:09:00,009 --> 01:09:01,210
Take this.

669
01:09:14,276 --> 01:09:16,111
<font color="#ffff54">Everything's fine.</font>

670
01:09:18,572 --> 01:09:20,365
<font color="#ffff54">Everything's fine.</font>

671
01:09:28,170 --> 01:09:31,606
I think they
impregnate women at the resort.

672
01:10:00,635 --> 01:10:03,239
After my mom died,

673
01:10:03,638 --> 01:10:06,142
I accidentally called
our house...

674
01:10:07,742 --> 01:10:10,845
and I heard her voice
on the answering machine.

675
01:10:13,715 --> 01:10:16,018
It kind of helped,

676
01:10:17,386 --> 01:10:19,221
so I kept calling.

677
01:10:22,057 --> 01:10:24,326
Maybe you can do that too.

678
01:11:09,405 --> 01:11:12,141
<i>Do you know what this bird</i>
<i>is famous for?</i>

679
01:11:15,211 --> 01:11:20,683
This bird lays its eggs
in the nests
of other bird species

680
01:11:20,983 --> 01:11:25,720
and then lets those birds
raise its offspring.

681
01:11:28,591 --> 01:11:30,725
No! Not in here!

682
01:12:01,090 --> 01:12:04,026
Your parents spent
their honeymoon here?

683
01:12:14,802 --> 01:12:17,506
How old is your sister?

684
01:12:23,245 --> 01:12:24,480
Gretchen?

685
01:12:25,981 --> 01:12:27,750
Yes, I am fine.

686
01:12:28,150 --> 01:12:30,486
<i>We are in the treatment center</i>
<i>by the hospital.</i>

687
01:12:30,653 --> 01:12:31,853
-If you come back
in the morning,

688
01:12:32,288 --> 01:12:34,256
Alma won't even know
you were gone.

689
01:12:34,423 --> 01:12:36,759
<i>Alma is going</i>
<i>to stay here for the evening.</i>

690
01:12:36,858 --> 01:12:39,261
<i>Dr. Bonomo is going to monitor</i>
<i>her sleep.</i>

691
01:12:39,361 --> 01:12:40,129
<i>Dad?</i>

692
01:12:40,229 --> 01:12:41,697
<i>-Beth and I are coming home.</i>

693
01:12:41,863 --> 01:12:43,931
Dad, I really need
to talk to you about--

694
01:12:45,933 --> 01:12:47,835
<i>-What is it, Gretchen?</i>

695
01:12:48,971 --> 01:12:51,006
We can't trust them.

696
01:12:51,440 --> 01:12:53,442
<i>-Gretchen, we can talk</i>
<i>when we're home.</i>

697
01:12:53,542 --> 01:12:56,378
<i>I told you</i>
<i>I will protect you.</i>

698
01:13:00,249 --> 01:13:01,550
<i>Get ready.</i>

699
01:13:01,849 --> 01:13:03,552
What's wrong with Beth?

700
01:13:19,034 --> 01:13:22,404
<i>Dr. Bonomo, June 21st.</i>

701
01:13:24,106 --> 01:13:28,444
This is homo-cuculidae, Alma.

702
01:13:29,244 --> 01:13:33,716
<i>Astonishing resemblance</i>
<i>to her surrogate mother, Beth.</i>

703
01:13:34,183 --> 01:13:38,120
<i>The surrogate mother's distress</i>
<i>grows in close proximity</i>

704
01:13:38,253 --> 01:13:40,155
<i>to the biological mother.</i>

705
01:13:40,456 --> 01:13:44,493
<i>Thus both host parents</i>
<i>have been removed</i>
<i>from the premises.</i>

706
01:13:47,262 --> 01:13:50,299
Compared to animal brood
parasites,

707
01:13:50,399 --> 01:13:55,371
homo-cuculidae developed
a unique evolutionary trait.

708
01:13:55,571 --> 01:13:59,874
<i>Instead of leaving</i>
<i>their offspring</i>
<i>in the care of a host,</i>

709
01:13:59,975 --> 01:14:04,213
<i>homo-cuculidae returns</i>
<i>to claim their young.</i>

710
01:14:04,780 --> 01:14:06,515
Contact with the biological
mother

711
01:14:06,615 --> 01:14:10,252
speeds up the process
of the offspring's physical
development

712
01:14:10,519 --> 01:14:13,956
<i>and its abilities</i>
<i>significantly.</i>

713
01:14:17,393 --> 01:14:22,698
We are about to initiate
the first close-distance
encounter

714
01:14:22,998 --> 01:14:25,100
with the biological mother.

715
01:14:45,053 --> 01:14:46,921
Brood parasites.

716
01:14:49,558 --> 01:14:51,393
<i>They don't impregnate.</i>

717
01:14:51,560 --> 01:14:54,129
They implant eggs.

718
01:14:56,365 --> 01:14:59,435
My wife and I tried
to get pregnant.

719
01:15:02,037 --> 01:15:05,574
I was supposed to fertilize
that egg.

720
01:15:08,510 --> 01:15:10,012
Like your father...

721
01:15:11,180 --> 01:15:12,748
<i>on his honeymoon.</i>

722
01:15:15,017 --> 01:15:17,019
<i>And then what do they do?</i>

723
01:15:18,720 --> 01:15:20,689
Release them into the wild.

724
01:15:22,858 --> 01:15:25,461
When the mother shows up...

725
01:15:25,561 --> 01:15:27,696
I end this experiment.

726
01:15:29,565 --> 01:15:31,633
What about my sister?

727
01:15:34,236 --> 01:15:37,339
That is not your sister.

728
01:15:39,041 --> 01:15:40,375
Two.

729
01:15:40,542 --> 01:15:42,678
<i>Yeah, the sister</i>
<i>of the young one</i>

730
01:15:42,778 --> 01:15:45,013
and a rogue police detective.

731
01:15:45,547 --> 01:15:49,518
<i>Yeah, I am afraid we must</i>
<i>commence definitive measures</i>
<i>immediately.</i>

732
01:15:50,085 --> 01:15:51,353
<i>She's dead.</i>

733
01:15:52,554 --> 01:15:54,590
The feather
I wrote my name with.

734
01:15:55,591 --> 01:15:58,093
<i>The plumage</i>
<i>of the apportioners.</i>

735
01:16:02,684 --> 01:16:05,103
<font color="#ffff54">We're in the middle of an experiment.</font>

736
01:16:05,228 --> 01:16:07,605
<font color="#ffff54">What happened? You're bleeding.</font>

737
01:16:08,398 --> 01:16:11,234
<font color="#ffff54">The recordings you made
behind my back...</font>

738
01:16:11,359 --> 01:16:14,612
<font color="#ffff54">Are they still under the staircase
at your house?</font>

739
01:16:19,748 --> 01:16:20,749
Yeah.

740
01:16:24,038 --> 01:16:25,873
<font color="#ffff54">I'm sorry, Danielle.</font>

741
01:16:48,143 --> 01:16:49,478
No! No!

742
01:16:58,453 --> 01:17:00,322
I'm not going to hurt you.

743
01:17:35,791 --> 01:17:37,793
Alma. Alma?

744
01:17:38,093 --> 01:17:40,095
Alma, we have to go.

745
01:17:40,262 --> 01:17:42,164
We have to go now.

746
01:18:09,725 --> 01:18:11,159
Just stay right here.

747
01:19:02,778 --> 01:19:05,280
Cover your ears
and stay close to me.

748
01:19:50,892 --> 01:19:52,427
Alma?

749
01:27:39,338 --> 01:27:41,173
<font color="#ffff54">Mr. König!</font>

750
01:27:41,796 --> 01:27:43,332
She's dead!

751
01:27:44,133 --> 01:27:45,668
Mom is dead!

752
01:27:46,235 --> 01:27:50,705
<i>Where's your machine gun,</i>
<i>my dear?</i>

753
01:27:50,973 --> 01:27:53,142
Is it under your cast, huh?

754
01:27:56,278 --> 01:27:57,246
Why me?

755
01:27:57,346 --> 01:28:00,115
It's not about you,
you little brat.

756
01:28:00,915 --> 01:28:03,586
This is nature.

757
01:28:03,686 --> 01:28:06,055
<i>She is supposed</i>
<i>to be focusing...</i>

758
01:28:06,155 --> 01:28:09,757
<i>on reproduction and breeding.</i>

759
01:28:10,159 --> 01:28:16,332
And you are competing
for resources
with her offspring.

760
01:28:16,599 --> 01:28:19,101
<i>Our process here ensures</i>

761
01:28:19,201 --> 01:28:22,037
<i>that each new generation</i>
<i>we breed</i>

762
01:28:22,137 --> 01:28:24,939
<i>is more powerful than the last.</i>

763
01:28:25,107 --> 01:28:28,477
<i>And my dear,</i>
<i>when I am done with you</i>

764
01:28:28,776 --> 01:28:31,447
<i>and reunite Alma with--</i>

765
01:29:51,345 --> 01:29:53,847
<font color="#ffff54">I'm sorry.</font>

766
01:29:58,352 --> 01:30:05,109
<font color="#ffff54">I would never hurt you.</font>

767
01:30:08,410 --> 01:30:11,447
Stay away
from her, Alma.

768
01:30:12,491 --> 01:30:17,996
<font color="#ffff54">We have to leave now.</font>

769
01:30:34,680 --> 01:30:38,767
<font color="#ffff54">My mom called.</font>

770
01:30:47,276 --> 01:30:52,156
<font color="#ffff54">She got your message.</font>

771
01:31:00,080 --> 01:31:02,791
<font color="#ffff54">Will she come to visit?</font>

772
01:31:09,872 --> 01:31:11,140
No.

773
01:31:12,441 --> 01:31:15,677
S-She... can't.

774
01:31:17,813 --> 01:31:22,985
But she says thank you.

775
01:31:23,918 --> 01:31:26,088
Thank you, Alma.

776
01:31:57,085 --> 01:31:59,154
Thank you, Alma.

777
01:32:06,795 --> 01:32:09,097
I really need your help.

778
01:32:21,844 --> 01:32:23,645
<i>Henry!</i>

779
01:32:24,146 --> 01:32:26,415
<i>You said you'll protect me.</i>

780
01:32:29,718 --> 01:32:31,320
I stand by it.

781
01:32:31,753 --> 01:32:34,656
<i>-Did you ever tell your wife</i>
<i>you'd protect her?</i>

782
01:32:39,061 --> 01:32:40,496
What?

783
01:32:42,297 --> 01:32:46,335
<i>Did you tell her</i>
<i>you'd protect her?</i>

784
01:32:51,473 --> 01:32:52,574
<i>Did you?</i>

785
01:32:56,845 --> 01:32:59,248
Yes!

786
01:32:59,348 --> 01:33:02,017
<i>-Okay, we are coming out now.</i>

787
01:33:27,676 --> 01:33:29,144
Alma!

788
01:33:29,511 --> 01:33:32,447
I need you to come
to me now, my angel.

789
01:33:34,349 --> 01:33:36,485
<i>What are you doing?</i>

790
01:33:36,585 --> 01:33:37,853
She's one of them!

791
01:33:38,086 --> 01:33:39,922
<i>Alma!</i>

792
01:33:40,023 --> 01:33:41,323
I don't think so.

793
01:33:41,523 --> 01:33:42,491
<i>-Come to me.</i>

794
01:33:43,158 --> 01:33:45,260
She will be.

795
01:33:45,527 --> 01:33:47,563
She will become!

796
01:33:48,163 --> 01:33:50,699
- I don't think so.
<i>- Alma!</i>

797
01:33:50,866 --> 01:33:53,068
<i>We need to find out</i>
<i>how many there are.</i>

798
01:33:53,168 --> 01:33:56,505
I need to take my sister
away from this place.

799
01:33:57,205 --> 01:33:59,474
-Stop!
-Let her go.

800
01:33:59,808 --> 01:34:03,012
Let her go, she's destined
to become a mother.

801
01:34:03,111 --> 01:34:04,846
She is not your sister!

802
01:34:04,947 --> 01:34:06,181
They stopped reproducing before.

803
01:34:06,281 --> 01:34:08,550
They will go extinct
without preservation.

804
01:34:08,717 --> 01:34:10,252
Oh, they will go extinct.

805
01:34:10,352 --> 01:34:12,321
<i>-Hundreds of years of research.</i>

806
01:34:12,421 --> 01:34:14,523
<i>This is the will</i>
<i>of the apportioners.</i>

807
01:34:14,690 --> 01:34:16,191
<i>Let her go.</i>

808
01:34:16,725 --> 01:34:18,594
You don't know
what you're doing!

